This is the interesting story of Enugu based woman of God Prophetess Patience Egbogu who is currently Head Pastor at Christ Healing Prayer Deliverance church, CHPDC. The church located at 21 Imo River behind 2nd bus stop Abakpa Nike area of the Coal city where many people have started depending on the church for spiritual upliftment. Her full names are NDIDIAMAKA Patience  Egbogu nee Anyim  from Ovim , AKAEZE  in  EBONYI STATE.  She was called to service of the. LORD about 2006 while living with her aunt at 82 division of the Nigerian Army Enugu. The fellowship began in the sitting room of their house with her aunt’s children and a few neighbors as congregants. She also hosted  Counseling days at the Mammy market shop where her aunty  sold groceries on a particular day of the week. At a time when the living room could no longer contain them, they had to move outside the house under a Melina tree. From the melina tree, the fellowship had to move again to the Army Children Primary School of the 82 Division. The fellowship continued to grow in numerical strenght and a permanent site was  now required  and God provided the present site much sooner than later. Prophetess Egbogu is noted for her vibrant preaching punctuated by a sonorous voice in spontneous eruption into songs, -Advertisement- POLL In a chat recently, the woman of God said her “life and ministry is in God’s hands. Only God directs my action. Whatever you see is the handiwork of God in whose loins I am tied “ Asked about the future of her ministry, she exclaims “Only God knows everything”